cs.HC, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SD

The paper discusses concepts related to human computation, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also reviews information theory (cs.IT) and different types of computation, which could fall under the categories of algorithms (cs.DS) or theory of computation (cs.CC). The examples used in the paper, online social networks and Wikipedia, could fall under the categories of social networks (cs.SI) or web technologies (cs.CY). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.HC, followed by cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.CY, and cs.SD (software engineering).
